# SecureCoder ignore file
# Exclude files from security scanning using glob patterns, one per line.
# Patterns are matched against the full absolute file path.
# Lines starting with # are comments. Blank lines are ignored.
#
# Examples:
#   *test*          - ignore any file whose path contains "test"
#   *_test.*        - ignore files ending in _test.<ext>
#   **/*_test.*     - same, across any directory depth
#   **/test/**      - ignore everything inside a "test" directory
#   vendor/**       - ignore all files in vendor/
#   *.generated.*   - ignore generated files

# --- Test files (enabled by default) ---
*test.*
*_test.*
**/*_test.*
**/test/**

# --- Generated/vendored files (uncomment to enable) ---
# vendor/**
# *.generated.*
# *.pb.go